The paper deals with the complexity of equivalence and learning for tree automata, which is a topic that falls under the category of formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). The paper also discusses the relationship between equivalence testing and polynomial identity testing, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The lower bounds on the number of queries needed for learning also suggest that the paper could belong to the category of computational learning theory (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of weighted tree automata and fields suggests that the paper could also belong to the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
